# Environment Variables Configuration

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the required values.

## Analytics & Tracking
```
# Google Analytics 4 Measurement ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Meta (Facebook) Pixel ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_META_PIXEL_ID=XXXXXXXXXX

# LinkedIn Insight Partner ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_LINKEDIN_PARTNER_ID=XXXXXXX
```

## Security & Forms
```
# Google reCAPTCHA v3 Keys
NEXT_PUBLIC_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=6LcXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
RECAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY=6LUXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# Email Service (Resend)
RESEND_API_KEY=re_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# Optional: SendGrid fallback
SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
SMTP_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=apikey
SMTP_PASS=SG.XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
```

## External Services
```
# Edunext Parent Portal URL
EDUNEXT_URL=https://sdpsis.edunexttechnologies.com

# Error Monitoring (Sentry)
SENTRY_DSN=https://XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX@oXXXXXX.ingest.sentry.io/XXXXXXX
SENTRY_ORG=sdps-school
SENTRY_PROJECT=website
```

## Application Settings
```
# Site URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.sdpsinternationalschool.com

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production
```

## CBSE Compliance Info
```
# School Identification (for metadata)
CBSE_AFFILIATION_NUMBER=1030747
CBSE_SCHOOL_CODE=50716
```

## Rate Limiting
```
# Form Submission Limits
FORM_RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=3600000
FORM_RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=3
```

## File Upload Settings
```
# Max upload size in bytes (5MB)
MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE=5242880

# Allowed file types for resumes
ALLOWED_RESUME_TYPES=application/pdf,application/msword,application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document
```

---

## Setup Instructions

1. Copy this file:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env.local
   ```

2. Fill in all required values from your service dashboards:
   - GA4: https://analytics.google.com/
   - Meta Pixel: https://business.facebook.com/events_manager/
   - LinkedIn Tag: https://www.linkedin.com/campaigns/accounts/
   - reCAPTCHA: https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin
   - Resend: https://resend.com/api-keys
   - Sentry: https://sentry.io/settings/

3. Verify environment variables are loaded:
   ```bash
   npm run build
   ```

4. Test form submissions and analytics in development:
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

## Security Notes

- ⚠️ **NEVER** commit `.env.local` to version control
- ✅ `.env.example` should contain placeholder values only
- 🔐 Rotate API keys every 90 days
- 📝 Keep a secure backup of all credentials
- 🔍 Use different keys for development and production

## Verification Commands

```bash
# Check if all required env vars are set
grep -E "^NEXT_PUBLIC_|^RESEND_|^SENTRY_" .env.local | wc -l

# Should return at least 8 lines

# Test build with current env vars
npm run typecheck && npm run build
```
